<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1629,1871]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1702,1728]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Notes on morphology.</emphasis>
Body very small (TL 
<quantity box="[712,817,1701,1728]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="1.85">1.85 mm</quantity>
), brownish black, covered with erect setae. Apical por- tion of each elytron with small opaque area covered by dense, stout, black setae. Gonocoxites membranous, gonostyli apical (
<figureCitation box="[289,382,1773,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,195,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[151,1436,195,1889]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 27. Calvariopsis gen. nov., females. A–B) C. sp., Bolivia; C–D) C. sp., Colombia; E–G) C. sp., Costa Rica; H) C. sp., Ecuador; I) C. sp., Ecuador; J) C. sp., French Guiana; K) C. sp., Panama; L) C. sp., Paraguay; M) C. sp., Peru. A, H, I–M) genital tract; B, G) bursal sclerite; C), E) ovipositor; D, F) sternite VIII." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2783802/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Fig. 
<date box="[341,382,1773,1799]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1927-01">27I</date>
</figureCitation>
), bursal sclerite rod-like, long.
</paragraph>
